        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 1:20PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 120 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Beech Mountain, or 6 miles north of Elk Park, moving
east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Banner Elk, Elk Park, Beech Mountain In Avery County, Sugar Mountain,
Seven Devils, and Grandfather Mountain State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
